# Accessibility (Minimal)

Not a full WCAG audit — baseline so the app is usable with keyboard and screen readers.

## Required

- **Dialogs:** always include `DialogTitle` (visually hidden OK via `className="sr-only"` if no visible title)
- **Icon-only buttons:** `title` attribute or `aria-label` — match `Sidebar.tsx` nav pattern
- **Form fields:** pair `Label` + `Input`/`Select`; don't rely on placeholder alone
- **Destructive actions:** confirm dialog or `confirm()` — already used for deletes in settings

## Prefer

- Semantic HTML: `<button>` not `<div onClick>`
- Focus visible on interactive elements (shadcn defaults)
- Don't remove `alt`/`aria-*` when editing existing components

## Skip unless asked

- Full keyboard nav audit
- ARIA live regions for toasts (sonner handles basics)
- High-contrast theme beyond existing CSS variables
